{"title":"SRAM Adds a More Affordable Eagle Transmission Group – for OE only, Plus new Brakes!","link":"https://bikerumor.com/sram-adds-a-more-affordable-eagle-transmission-group-for-oe-only-plus-new-brakes/","date":1719928800000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-S-1000-derailleur-hero.jpeg\" width=\"1280\" height=\"799\" alt=\"(Photos/SRAM)\" /></p>\n<p>SRAM’s Transmissions have been getting all the attention for MTB drivetrains lately, and now there’s a new one. Only, this one will only be available if you buy a complete bike along with it. The new S-1000 Eagle Transmission promises to be the most affordable option yet, but for now, you’ll only find it on complete bikes as an OE spec. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Along with S-1000, SRAM is also introducing the new DB8 Stealth brakes. SRAM says that both of these product offerings are aimed at delivering the dream of robust performance for more riders.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s get right into it. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>SRAM DB8 Stealth</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-DBlever-e1719877618975.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-DBlever-e1719877618975.jpeg\" alt=\"SRAM DB8 Brakes and S-1000 T-Type Transmission DBlever\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-DBlever-e1719877618975.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-DBlever-e1719877618975-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-DBlever-e1719877618975-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-DBlever-e1719877618975-768x576.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-Db8-blever-rotated-1-e1719877693966.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"928\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-Db8-blever-rotated-1-e1719877693966.jpeg\" alt=\"SRAM DB8 Brakes and S-1000 T-Type Transmission Db8 blever rotated\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-Db8-blever-rotated-1-e1719877693966.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-Db8-blever-rotated-1-e1719877693966-297x215.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-Db8-blever-rotated-1-e1719877693966-120x87.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-Db8-blever-rotated-1-e1719877693966-768x557.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The DB8 is SRAM’s simple, robust, and powerful brake for riders who prefer the set-and-forget. It uses a low-maintenance mineral oil paired with proven lever technology. It also features easy adjustment access and superior ergonomic comfort. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-DB8-Caliper-closeup.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-DB8-Caliper-closeup.jpeg\" alt=\"SRAM DB8 Brakes and S-1000 T-Type Transmission DB8 Caliper closeup\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-DB8-Caliper-closeup.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-DB8-Caliper-closeup-297x297.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-DB8-Caliper-closeup-120x120.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-DB8-Caliper-closeup-768x768.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-DB8-caliper.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-DB8-caliper.jpeg\" alt=\"SRAM DB8 Brakes and S-1000 T-Type Transmission DB8 caliper\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-DB8-caliper.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-DB8-caliper-297x297.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-DB8-caliper-120x120.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-DB8-caliper-768x768.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The stealth lever body design brings the hose parallel to the bar, allowing for a sleeker, more modern ride. SRAM says it shouldn’t be a surprise that they have “Code-like power” as the DB8 Stealth utilizes similar caliper architecture and existing brake pads. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-DB8-caliper-and-rotor-full.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-DB8-caliper-and-rotor-full.jpeg\" alt=\"SRAM DB8 Brakes and S-1000 T-Type Transmission DB8 caliper and rotor full\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-DB8-caliper-and-rotor-full.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-DB8-caliper-and-rotor-full-297x297.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-DB8-caliper-and-rotor-full-120x120.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-DB8-caliper-and-rotor-full-768x768.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-DB8-claiper-and-rotor.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-DB8-claiper-and-rotor.jpeg\" alt=\"SRAM DB8 Brakes and S-1000 T-Type Transmission DB8 claiper and rotor\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-DB8-claiper-and-rotor.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-DB8-claiper-and-rotor-297x297.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-DB8-claiper-and-rotor-120x120.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-DB8-claiper-and-rotor-768x768.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>DB8 Stealth Retail &amp; Features</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Retail: $137 – Disc Brake, Diffusion Black, front 950mm hose (includes MMX clamp, rotor/bracket sold separately) – Mineral Oil Brake B1<br />Retail: $137 – Disc Brake, Diffusion Black, rear 2000mm hose (includes MMX clamp, rotor/bracket sold separately) – Mineral Oil Brake B1</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Stealth lever architecture </li>\n\n\n\n<li>Code-like heavy-duty power</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Tooled lever reach adjust</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Uses existing Code pads</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Designed for use with Maxima Mineral Oil only</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Designed for use with SRAM Mineral Oil Bleed Kit only</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h3>DB8 Stealth Specs</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>SPECIFICATIONS</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure><table><tbody><tr><td>Application (DB)</td><td>MTB</td></tr><tr><td>Brake type</td><td>Hydraulic</td></tr><tr><td>Blade material</td><td>Aluminum</td></tr><tr><td>Color (DB)</td><td>Diffusion Black Anodized</td></tr><tr><td>Rec MMX clamp (not included)</td><td>MMX clamp, black, steel</td></tr><tr><td>Orientation</td><td>Front, Rear</td></tr><tr><td>Pad type (Disc)</td><td>Steel-backed organic</td></tr><tr><td>Bracket (Disc Brake)</td><td>Direct mount DIR</td></tr><tr><td>Hose length (mm)</td><td>2000mm, 950mm</td></tr><tr><td>Rotor (AM only)</td><td>n/a</td></tr><tr><td>Pistons</td><td>4</td></tr><tr><td>Piston material</td><td>Phenolic Plastic</td></tr><tr><td>Rotor type recommended</td><td>1-piece CenterLine</td></tr><tr><td>Clamp Included (DB)</td><td>Yes – MMX Clamp</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>SRAM S-1000 Eagle Transmission</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>SRAM is confident that the introduction of the new T-Type S-1000 Eagle to the Eagle Transmission Ecosystem will make Eagle T-type Transmissions more attainable to more riders. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>SRAM S-1000 Eagle Crankset</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-S-1000-cranks-e1719877729139.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"480\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-S-1000-cranks-e1719877729139.jpeg\" alt=\"SRAM DB8 Brakes and S-1000 T-Type Transmission S-1000 cranks\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-S-1000-cranks-e1719877729139.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-S-1000-cranks-e1719877729139-297x111.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-S-1000-cranks-e1719877729139-120x45.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-S-1000-cranks-e1719877729139-768x288.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The S-1000 Transmission crankset offers a sleek, sturdy crankarm that’s engineered to be both robust and reliable. Like other cranks in the Transmission ecosystem, the S-1000 crank features 8-bolt ring compatibility. It also offers a stamped steel or aluminum ring with optional bash guards.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-crank-arms-e1719877763755.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"290\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-crank-arms-e1719877763755.jpeg\" alt=\"SRAM DB8 Brakes and S-1000 T-Type Transmission crank arms\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-crank-arms-e1719877763755.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-crank-arms-e1719877763755-297x67.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-crank-arms-e1719877763755-120x27.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-crank-arms-e1719877763755-768x174.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Allowing for aftermarket customization, the chainrings are cross-compatible with chainring and bash guard options. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>S-1000 Eagle Crankset Features</h3>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Forged aluminum crankarm with 8-bolt ring compatibility</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Integrated composite bash guards shared with GX and X0 Eagle Transmission</li>\n\n\n\n<li>155mm, 160mm, 165mm, 170mm, 175mm lengths</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Stamped steel or aluminum chainrings</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Compatible with all SRAM T-Type components</li>\n\n\n\n<li>OE availability only</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h3>S-1000 Eagle Derailleur</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-S-1000-derailleur-e1719877799100.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"1164\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-S-1000-derailleur-e1719877799100.jpeg\" alt=\"SRAM DB8 Brakes and S-1000 T-Type Transmission S-1000 derailleur\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-S-1000-derailleur-e1719877799100.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-S-1000-derailleur-e1719877799100-297x270.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-S-1000-derailleur-e1719877799100-120x109.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-S-1000-derailleur-e1719877799100-768x698.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This derailleur is the entry point to the Eagle Transmission ecosystem. The S-1000 Eagle Derailleur has the same architecture as SRAM’s GX Eagle Transmission. The full-mount design mounts around the wheel’s axle on UDH-equipped bikes. It also includes what SRAM calls Cassette Mapping, or “the marriage of the derailleur’s firmware and hardware to our T-Type cassettes, helps deliver the best shift under load. Even under the added power of an eMTB.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Like all of the Eagle Transmission derailleurs, the S-1000 is rebuildable. It has replaceable skid plates and a two-piece outer link. It has a removable cage assembly that simply rotates off. Featuring a sleek black-on-black appearance means that it can be mixed and matched with other T-Type ecosystem components.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The S-1000 also features SRAM’s new Drag Spring Cage Damper for reliable chain retention and long-term reliability. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>The S-1000 Eagle Derailleur Features</h3>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Compatible with all SRAM T-Type components</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Shares GX Eagle Transmission architecture with a sleek black colorway</li>\n\n\n\n<li>New drag spring cage damper</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Hangerless Interface, Full Mount attachment method</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Radically clear setup process, no adjustment required</li>\n\n\n\n<li>OE availability only</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h3>SRAM XS-1270 Eagle Cassette</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-cassette-e1719877829158.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"1156\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-cassette-e1719877829158.jpeg\" alt=\"SRAM DB8 Brakes and S-1000 T-Type Transmission cassette\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-cassette-e1719877829158.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-cassette-e1719877829158-297x268.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-cassette-e1719877829158-120x108.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SRAM-DB8-Brakes-and-S-1000-T-Type-Transmission-cassette-e1719877829158-768x694.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Sporting the same medal-winning technology as the other Transmission cassettes in the Eagle family, the XS-1270 offers incredible performance for more riders. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Finished in a unique nickel chrome, this cassette promises to be quiet, durable, and features a replaceable gear cluster. And for the first time on a traditional HG splined driver body, the XS-1270 features a full 10-52t range thanks to the integration of the 10th tooth and lockring.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>The XS-1270 Eagle Cassette Features</h3>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Complete 10-52t range</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Gears 8-12 (10-12-14-16-18t) are a replaceable cluster</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Splined 8, 9, 10 Speed Driverbody compatible – steel Driverbody material required</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Full X-SYNC design for best-ever inboard and outboard shifting performance under load</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Unique black nickel chrome finish</li>\n\n\n\n<li>55mm chain line compatibility for a more moderate chain angle, longer wear, and greater precision. Setup Cog for simple setup</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Compatible with all SRAM T-Type components</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/sram-adds-a-more-affordable-eagle-transmission-group-for-oe-only-plus-new-brakes/\">SRAM Adds a More Affordable Eagle Transmission Group – for OE only, Plus new Brakes!</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"8e93302dc23fd6cd5b9240e13ef2477ea40a2c16f55477d41b1104df1cd3ab99","category":"Cycling"}